				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
							<p>From the &#8220;Vertices&#8221;, &#8220;Half-Edges&#8221; and &#8220;Faces&#8221; list on the GUI, clicking any element of the list will highlight the corresponding elements on the mesh. The selected vertex is highlighted as a white dot, the selected face as a colored outline, and the selected half-edge as a red-yellow gradient line segment. In addition, the following keypress events are also implemented:</p><ul><li>N to go to the next half-edge</li><li>M to go to the symmetric half-edge</li><li>V to highlight the vertex of the selected half-edge</li><li>F to highlight the face of the selected half-edge</li><li>H to highlight the half-edge of the currently selected vertex</li><li>Shift + H to highlight the half-edge of the currently selected face</li></ul>						</div>
